your%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20seek%20out%20mini-retirement%20for%20many%20reasons.%20Millennials%20are%20entering%20their%20second%20or%20third%20decade%20in%20the%20workforce.%20No%20longer%20new%20to%20the%20job%20market%2C%20perhaps%20they're%20evaluating%20what%20direction%20to%20take%20their%20career%20next.%20Or%20maybe%20they're%20trying%20to%20balance%20their%20career%20with%20young%20children.%20These%20big%20life%20changes%20make%20a%20mini-retirement%20especially%20appealing%20to%20Johnsrud's%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20as%20serious%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-deal-with-stress-burnout-work-mental-health-professional-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eburnout%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20although%20Johnsrud%20certainly%20sees%20many%20cases%20of%20that.%20A%20mini-retirement%20can%20help%20people%20redefine%20their%20professional%20lives%20and%20shape%20their%20work%20into%20something%20more%20fulfilling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Google%2C%20Poirel%20was%20experiencing%20decreased%20motivation%20and%20energy%20and%20an%20increase%20in%20work-related%20stress.%20Poirel%20sees%20her%20mini-retirement%20as%20a%20way%20to%20steer%20her%20career%20away%20from%20corporate%20goalposts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BObviously%20there%20are%20ups%20and%20downs%20to%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Poirel%20said%20of%20workplace%20stress.%20But%20after%20finding%20herself%20experiencing%20heightened%20levels%20of%20dissatisfaction%20for%20many%20months%2C%20Poirel%20took%20it%20as%20a%20sign%20to%20take%20a%20break.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20her%20mini-retirement%20ends%20in%20September%2C%20Poirel%20plans%20to%20look%20for%20a%20job%20at%20a%20company%20focused%20on%20sustainability%2C%20a%20topic%20that%20aligns%20with%20her%20own%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20not%20interested%20at%20all%20in%20climbing%20the%20ladder%20anymore.%20Higher%20job%20titles%20mean%20more%20responsibilities%2C%20more%20stress%2C%20more%20working%20hours%2C%20and%20that's%20really%20not%20something%20I%20want%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Li%2C%20his%20career%20priorities%20have%20changed%20over%20time.%20While%20Li%20has%20gotten%20a%20lot%20experience%20working%20in%20the%20startup%20space%2C%20but%20he's%20looking%20to%20expand%20his%20skill%20set%20for%20the%20next%20chapter%20of%20his%20career%20and%20work%20in%20a%20different%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20boxes%20that%20I'm%20checking%20now%20are%20fundamentally%20different%20than%20the%20boxes%20that%20I%20was%20checking%20before%20my%20career%20break%2C%26quot%3B%20Li%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d5fcf46a-a8b8-45f6-b835-f25becc7d7ec%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20things%20can't%20wait%20until%2065%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMini-retirees%20don't%20agree%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20waiting%20until%20your%20sixties%20to%20enjoy%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20especially%20true%20for%20Poirel%2C%20whose%20partner%20is%2017%20years%20older%20than%20her.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I'm%2060%2C%20he's%20going%20to%20be%2077.%20That%20doesn't%20sound%20fun%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPoirel%20also%20spent%20a%20month%20with%20her%20family%20earlier%20in%20her%20mini-retirement%20%E2%80%94%20something%20she%20hasn't%20done%20since%20she%20was%20a%20student.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20young%20children%20can%20also%20be%20a%20catalyst%20for%20a%20mini-retirement.%20It%20definitely%20was%20for%20Johnsrud%2C%20who%20once%20took%20a%2010-week%20mini-retirement%20to%20go%20on%20a%20road%20trip%20with%20her%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20if%20we%20didn't%20do%20this%20now%2C%20I%20can't%20do%20this%20trip%20in%2020%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Johnsrud%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20way%2020%20and%2030-year-olds%20are%20going%20take%2010%20weeks%20out%20of%20their%20life%20to%20do%2010%20national%20parks%20in%