e%2C%20who%20talked%20about%20money%20on%20their%20first%20date%2C%20prioritize%20transparency%20and%20communication.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20discussed%20prenups%20and%20splitting%20expenses%20equitably%2C%20avoiding%20traditional%20gender%20roles.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20conversations%20with%20Tori%20Dunlap%2C%20a%2030-year-old%20Seattle-based%20financial%20educator%2C%20and%20her%20partner.%20They%20both%20asked%20that%20his%20identity%20be%20kept%20concealed%20for%20privacy%20reasons.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDunlap%20is%20the%20founder%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-start-business-with-no-money-her-first-100k-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EHer%20First%20100K%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20financial%20education%20company%20geared%20toward%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennial%20women.%20She%20is%20also%20a%20multimillionaire%2C%20New%20York%20Times%20best-selling%20author%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftori-dunlap-new-podcast-hit-top-spot-apple-charts-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Epodcast%20host%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHer%20partner%20has%20a%20graduate%20degree%20in%20athletics%20and%20works%20multiple%20jobs%20within%20the%20athletics%20and%20education%20space.%20He%20supplements%20his%20income%20with%20side%20gigs%20such%20as%20dog-sitting%20and%20private%20training%20and%20made%20around%20%2460%2C000%20in%202024.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20couple%20has%20been%20together%20for%20over%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years.%20They%20spoke%20with%20Business%20Insider%20to%20share%20how%20they%20manage%20and%20discuss%20money%20in%20their%20relationship.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20shows%20the%20back%20view%20of%20Tori%20Dunlap%20and%20her%20partner%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b8fb78c832c3638fa4f05c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETori%20Dunlap%20(right)%20and%20her%20partner%20(left)%20have%20been%20together%20for%20over%202.5%20years.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20courtesy%20of%20Tori%20Dunlap%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDunlap%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20started%20talking%20about%20money%20on%20our%20first%20date.%20By%20then%2C%20he%20knew%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-money-coach-shares-how-she-saved-100000-by-25-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efeminism%20was%20a%20huge%20part%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20my%20work%20and%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20bill%20came%2C%20I%20could%20tell%20there%20was%20some%20sort%20of%20internal%20conflict.%20He%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20really%20like%20to%20pay%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20offend%20you.%20Can%20I%20pay%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPartner%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20wasn't%20sure%20what%20the%20expectation%20was%20in%20terms%20of%20who%20pays%20or%20splitting%20the%20bill%2C%20so%20that%20was%20my%20way%20of%20saying%20that%20I'd%20like%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20bill.%20The%20meal%20was%20something%20like%20%24100%2C%20which%20wasn't%20as%20much%20to%20Tori%2C%20but%20was%20quite%20a%20bit%20for%20me%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDunlap%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt%20was%20really%20sweet.%20For%20me%2C%20that%20was%20an%20immediate%20green%20flag%20that%20ended%20up%20being%20a%20good%20sign%20for%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-2023-how-talk-your-partner-about-money-without-fighting-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20conversations%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20our%20relationship.%20It's%20sometimes%20hard%20to%20have%20th