3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC9762769%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3Dincarceration%2520and%2520homelessness.-%2CThe%2520two%2520crises%2520interact%2520with%2520and%2520worsen%2520one%2520another.%2Cand%2520Urban%2520Development%252C%25202021).%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomelessness%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC10273494%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efood%20insecurity%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversal-basic-income-pros-and-cons%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGuaranteed%20basic%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20offers%20participants%20no-strings-attached%20payments%20%E2%80%94%20has%20been%20piloted%20across%20America%20as%20an%20approach%20to%20poverty%20reduction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cities%20aren't%20the%20only%20places%20that%20have%20tried%20similar%20cash%20aid%20programs%3A%20the%20Center%20for%20Employment%20Opportunities%20gave%20cash%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ceoworks.org%2Fassets%2Fdownloads%2FCEO-RCS-1-Pager.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eover%2010%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20formerly%20incarcerated%20people%20across%20the%20US%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Gainesville%2C%20115%20participants%20received%20an%20initial%20%241%2C000%20payment%20followed%20by%20%24600%20a%20month%20for%2011%20months%2C%20ending%20in%20spring%202023.%20In%20Durham%2C%20109%20participants%20received%20%24600%20a%20month%20for%20one%20year%2C%20ending%20in%20spring%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20participant%20cohorts%20were%20compared%20to%20control%20groups%20of%20formerly%20incarcerated%20people%20who%20did%20not%20receive%20GBI%2C%20and%20the%20pilot%20results%20were%20published%20by%20the%20Center%20for%20Guaranteed%20Income%20Research%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%20in%20February.%20The%20results%20are%20based%20on%20interviews%20with%20participants%20and%20surveys%20that%20were%20completed%20before%2C%20during%2C%20and%20six%20months%20after%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20Gainesville%20and%20Durham%20participants%20struggled%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falabama-basic-income-single-mothers-afford-childcare-bills-birmingham-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emaintain%20financial%20gains%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20their%20cash%20payments%20ended%2C%20most%20said%20the%20money%20allowed%20them%20to%20afford%20essentials%20and%20alleviated%20some%20stress%2C%20which%20helped%20their%20mental%20health.%20Rent%2C%20groceries%2C%20and%20household%20bills%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewere%20commonly%20reported%20uses%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-helps-parents-afford-toys-children-improves-quality-life-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGBI%20payments%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGuaranteed%20income%20really%20is%20just%20a%20tool%20to%20ensure%2C%20in%20the%20Gainesville%20and%20Durham%20cases%20especially%2C%20that%20no%20one%20is%20too%20poor%20to%20be%20free%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sukhi%20Samra%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20advocacy%20group%20Mayors%20for%20a%20Guaranteed%20Income%2C%20which%20partnered%20on%20the%20pilots.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20trapping%20people%20in%20a%20culture%20of%20poverty%20and%20in%20a%20culture%20of%20scarcity%20and%20lack.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ff13c4ba-88fc-406a-9817-173fd59de630%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECash%20helped%20formerly%20incarcerated%20people%20afford%20essentials%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFormerly%20incarcerated%20people%20face%20higher%20rates%20of%20financial%20insecurity%20and%20unemployment%20compared%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20population.%20This%20can%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20afford%20basic%20needs.%20Per%20data%20published%20by%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Justice%20Statistics%20in%202022%2C%20the%20most%20recent%20year%20available%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbjs.ojp.gov%2Fcontent%2Fpub%2Fpdf%2Feprfp10.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabout%20a%20third%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20formerly%20incarcerated%20individuals%20aren't%20hired%20in%20the%20four%20years%20after%20their%20release.%20Black%20people%20were%20also%20admitted%20to%20jail%20at%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewtrusts.org%2Fen%2Fresearch-and-analysis%2Fissue-briefs%2F2023%2F05%2Fracial-disparities-persist-in-many-us-jails%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour%20times%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20rate%20of%20white%20people%20as%20of%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20states%20give%20incarcerated%20people%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20money%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.themarshallproject.org%2F2019%2F09%2F10%2Fwhat-gate-money-can-and-cannot-buy%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Marshall%2520Project%2520reached%2520out%2Cmay%2520leave%2520with%2520no%2520money%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebetween%20%2410%20and%20%24200%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20when%20they%20leave%20a%20prison%20or%20jail.%20However%2C%20some%20states%20restrict%20access%20to%20safety%20nets%20for%20formally%20incarcerated%20people.%20For%20example%2C%20Florida%20prohibits%20people%20who%20have%20been%20convicted%20of%20drug%20trafficking%20from%20accessing%20safety%20nets%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsnap-alice-food-stamps-hunger-government-assitance-free-meals-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESNAP%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20TANF.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrianna%20Seid%2C%20a%20lawyer%20for%20the%20justice%20program%20at%20the%20Brennan%20Center%20for%20Justice%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%2410%20or%20%24200%20might%20help%20buy%20a%20train%20or%20bus%20ticket%20home%2C%20but%20it%20isn't%20near%20enough%20to%20pay%20court%20fees%2C%20lease%20an%20apartment%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-parents-afford-childcare-get-stable-jobs-gbi-ubi-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eafford%20childcare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20establish%20reliable%20transportation%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20if%20people%20face%20limited%20access%20to%20safety%20nets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20this%20idea%20that%20people%20get%20arrested%20or%20convicted%2C%20go%20to%20prison%2C%20and%20leave%2C%20and%20that's%20just%20the%20end%20of%20the%20punishment%2C%26quot%3B%20Seid%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20people%2C%20they%20don't%20understand%20the%20ways%20that%20we%20excessively%20and%20perpetually%20punish%20people%20for%20having%20a%20criminal%20conviction%2C%20and%20it%20really%20touches%20every%20area%20of%20your%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECash%20is%20a%20potential%20way%20to%20ease%20work%20and%20income%20barriers%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Gainesville%20pilot%2C%20participants%20reported%20that%20guaranteed%20basic%20income%20helped%20them%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-gbi-ubi-low-income-americans-afford-housing-food-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecure%20housing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20more%20hope%2C%20increase%20financial%20resiliency%2C%20and%20put%20food%20on%20the%20table.%20The%20share%20of%20participants%20who%20said%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Bworried%20about%20having%20enough%20food%26quot%3B%20decreased%20from%2059%25%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20program%20to%2049%25%20six%20months%20after%20payments%20ended.%20The%20number%20of%20participants%20employed%20full-time%20also%20increased%20from%2012%25%20to%2017%25%20during%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurham%20participants%20reported%20using%20GBI%20money%20to%20buy%20hygiene%20products%2C%20afford%20food%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-basic-income-artists-helped-pay-healthcare-bills-gbi-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebuild%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20percentage%20of%20participants%20%26quot%3Bworried%20about%20having%20enough%20food%26quot%3B%20also%20decreased%20from%2059%25%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20program%20to%2044%25%20six%20months%20after%20payments%20ended.%20Over%20that%20same%20period%2C%20the%20share%20of%20participants%20who%20felt%20they%20had%20enough%20money%20to%20support%20themselves%20rose%20from%203.7%25%20to%2018.35%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESamra%20added%20that%20many%20participants%20in%20both%20Gainesville%20and%20Durham%20said%20that%20having%20extra%20cash%20helped%20them%20better%20adhere%20to%20probation%20requirements%20and%20prevent%20further%20arrests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223a89ce7a-7422-41c1-9158-685553aaa612%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMany%20participants%20struggled%20with%20housing%20costs%20after%20the%20programs%20ended%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20months%20into%20receiving%20cash%2C%203%25%20of%20Gainesville%20participants%20said%20they%20were%20experiencing%20homelessness.%20But%20six%20months%20after%20GBI%20ended%2C%20that%20figure%20had%20risen%20to%2012%25.%20In%20Durham%2C%20results%20showed%20that%2029%25%20of%20participants%20were%20severely%20housing-cost-burdened%20six%20months%20into%20the%20program%2C%20a%20number%20that%20rose%20to%2041%25%20six%20months%20after%20payments%20ended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Samra%20said%20that%20guaranteed%20basic%20income%20isn't%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20cure-all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpoverty-line-leaves-behind-low-income-americans-snap-medicare-wic-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoverty%20solution%3C%2Fa%3E.%20GBI%20pilots%20are%20temporary%2C%20and%20she%20said%20the%20financial%20challenges%20some%20participants%20faced%20after%20the%20program%20show%20that%20more%20support%20is%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Samra%2C%20there's%20one%20major%20takeaway%20from%20the%20results%3A%20financial%20support%20is%20a%20step%20toward%20keeping%20people%20out%20of%20the%20prison%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20results%20show%20that%20if%20you%20provide%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20cash%20support%2C%20you're%20allowing%20folks%20the%20space%20and%20the%20ability%20to%20not%20only%20re-enter%20and%20breathe%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20prevent%20the%20sort%20of%20harm%20and%20activities%20that%20they%20wouldn't%20be%20doing%20if%20it%20weren't%20for%20a%20simple%20lack%20of%20cash.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-formerly-incarcerated-people-florida-north-carolina-housing-food-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740301382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b8b768eb4be2fff9a542eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-formerly-incarcerated-people-florida-north-carolina-housing-food-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gainesville%20and%20Durham%20gave%20formerly%20incarcerated%20residents%20%24600%20a%20month.%20It%20helped%20participants%20afford%20food%20and%20other%20essentials.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22allisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%20(Allie%20Kelly)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-formerly-incarcerated-people-florida-north-carolina-housing-food-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rohit%20Sharma's%20Epic%20Reply%20As%20Ravi%20Shastri%20Commits%20Faux%20Pas%20During%20Toss%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia%20captain%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Rohit%20Sharma%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fplayers%2F857-rohit-sharma-playerprofile%5C%22%3ERohit%20Sharma%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20a%20fun%20little%20chat%20with%20former%20head%20coach%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Ravi%20Shastri%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2