ps%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcdx2vwg8gq1o.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcdx2vwg8gq1o.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Former%20CM%20Atishi%20chosen%20leader%20of%20opposition%20in%20Delhi%20assembly%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740299267000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-118500895%2Cimgsize-41390.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fformer-delhi-cm-atishi-chosen-leader-of-opposition-in-delhi-assembly%2Farticleshow%2F118500913.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fformer-delhi-cm-atishi-chosen-leader-of-opposition-in-delhi-assembly%2Farticleshow%2F118500913.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Has%20Trump%20Abandoned%20Ukraine%20In%20Favour%20Of%20Russia%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDonald%20Trump%20has%20spent%20only%20a%20month%20in%20his%20second%20term%20as%20the%20US%20President.%20However%2C%20he%20has%20disrupted%20the%20international%20order%2C%20weakened%20the%20Western%20alliance%20and%20created%20a%20sense%20of%20insecurity%20and%20uncertainty%20among%20its%20members%2C%20surprising%20even%20some%20of%20his%20supporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20a%20paradigm%20shift%20in%20US%20foreign%20policy%20under%20Trump.%20He%20is%20now%20closer%20to%20Moscow%20than%20Washington's%20traditional%20allies.%20He%20has%20embraced%20the%20Kremlin's%20narrative%20on%20Ukraine%20and%20has%20sidelined%20US%20allies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20senior%20members%20of%20the%20Trump%20administration%20have%20denied%20that%20the%20US%20has%20abandoned%20Kyiv%20and%20ignored%20its%20European%20allies%2C%20Trump%20himself%20has%20not%20made%20any%20serious%20attempts%20to%20pacify%20Ukrainians%20and%20Europeans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EActions%20Speak%20Louder%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20closeness%20to%20Russia%20has%20been%20on%20display%20since%20he%20talked%20for%2090%20minutes%20on%20the%20phone%20with%20Russian%20leader%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20in%20which%20they%20agreed%20to%20start%20negotiations%20to%20end%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20which%20will%20mark%20its%20third%20anniversary%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20did%20speak%20to%20Zelenskyy%20soon%20after%20that%20call%20with%20Putin%2C%20but%20a%20nervous%20Ukrainian%20President%20warned%20that%20excluding%20his%20country%20from%20the%20talks%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20dangerous%E2%80%9D.%20Events%20after%20that%20only%20made%20Ukrainians%20feels%20sidelined.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20Vice%20President%2C%20JD%20Vance%2C%20met%20European%20leaders%20in%20Munich%20two%20days%20later.%20But%20his%20comment%20that%20Europe%20will%20not%20be%20included%20in%20the%20peace%20talks%20only%20helped%20fuelled%20the%20speculation%20that%20they%20were%20being%20left%20out%20of%20the%20future%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20is%20closer%20to%20their%20homes%20and%20in%20which%20they%20have%20invested%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20and%20effort%20since%20the%20Russian%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVance's%20meeting%20with%20Zelenskyy%20did%20not%20go%20well%20either%20as%20the%20Ukrainian%20leader%20refused%20to%20give%20access%20to%20the%20country's%20vast%20reserves%20of%20critical%20minerals%20unless%20he%20was%20given%20security%20guarantees.%20That%20angered%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnding%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20was%20Trump's%20major%20campaign%20promise.%20But%20hardly%20anyone%20expected%20him%20to%20brazenly%20take%20Russia's%20side%20and%20even%20blame%20Ukraine%20for%20the%20conflict%2C%20which%20he%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20Tuesday%2C%20a%20US%20delegation%20led%20by%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Marco%20Rubio%20met%20the%20Russian%20delegation%20headed%20by%20Foreign%20Minister%20Sergey%20Lavrov%20in%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20to%20discuss%20peace.%20Ukraine%20was%20not%20invited.%20Putin%E2%80%94who%20had%20been%20shunned%20by%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20since%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%E2%80%94was%20delighted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump-Zelenskyy%20Row%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20frustrated%20Zelenskyy%20dismissed%20the%20Riyadh%20talks%20as%20worthless.%20Trump%20did%20not%20like%20those%20comments%20and%20called%20the%20Ukraine%20President%20a%20dictator%2C%20even%20accusing%20him%20of%20starting%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZelenskyy%20said%20the%20US%20President%20was%20living%20in%20a%20Russian-made%20%E2%80%9Cdisinformation%20space%E2%80%9D.%20This%20infuriated%20Trump%2C%20who%20does%20not%20take%20kindly%20to%20any%20criticism.%20He%20described%20Zelenskyy%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20modestly%20successful%20comedian%E2%80%9D%20who%20%E2%80%9Ctalked%20the%20United%20States%20of%20America%20into%20spending%20%24350%20Billion%2C%20to%20go%20into%20a%20War%20that%20couldn't%20be%20won%2C%20that%20never%20had%20to%20start%2C%20but%20a%20War%20that%20he%2C%20without%20the%20U.S.%20and%20%E2%80%98TRUMP%2C'%20will%20never%20be%20able%20to%20settle.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20behaviour%20towards%20Zelenskyy%20is%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20Biden's%2C%20who%20had%20backed%20Ukraine%20against%20Russia%20with%20all%20the%20possible%20military%20and%20financial%20aid.%20President%20Biden%20travelled%20to%20Ukraine%20many%20times%20since%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20in%20February%202022%20to%20display%20his%20administration's%20full%20support.%20He%20also%20promised%20NATO%20membership%20to%20Ukraine%20at%20a%20future%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20was%20severely%20punished%20for%20invading%20Ukraine.%20The%20US%20joined%20hands%20with%20its%20allies%20to%20isolate%20Moscow.%20Russia%20faced%20tough%20sanctions%20and%20its%20assets%20in%20the%20West%20were%20seized.%20The%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20issued%20an%20arrest%20warrant%20against%20Putin%20for%20alleged%20war%20crimes%20in%20Ukraine.%20There%20were%20even%20plans%20to%20put%20Putin%20and%20his%20close%20allies%20on%20Nuremberg-style%20trials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUkraine's%20Distant%20Dream%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUntil%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20Ukraine's%20leader%20was%20talking%20about%20even%20liberating%20all%20its%20territory%2C%20including%20Crimea%2C%20which%20Russia%20annexed%20in%202014%2C%20with%20the%20help%20of%20Western%20military%20equipment.%20Ukraine%20even%20succeeded%20in%20occupying%20the%20Russian%20territory%20of%20Kursk%2C%20which%20it%20had%20thought%20would%20be%20used%20as%20a%20bargaining%20chip%20during%20negotiations%20with%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20all%20that%20now%20looks%20like%20a%20distant%20dream.%20With%20Trump%20back%20in%20the%20White%20House%2C%20Ukraine%20fears%20that%20Russia%20will%20be%20allowed%20to%20keep%20all%20the%20occupied%20territory%20as%20part%20of%20the%20deal%20to%20end%20the%20war.%20Kyiv%20is%20now%20likely%20to%20be%20denied%20NATO%20membership.%20That%20could%20be%20a%20promise%20to%20Russia%20to%20end%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20under%20Trump%20has%20now%20even%20opposed%20calling%20Russia%20an%20aggressor%20in%20a%20G-7%20statement%20being%20prepared%20to%20mark%20the%20third%20anniversary%20of%20the%20war.%20The%20US%20team%20removed%20the%20phrase%20from%20the%20first%20draft%2C%20which%20was%20prepared%20by%20Canada%2C%20the%20current%20holder%20of%20the%20group's%20presidency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEuropeans%20Are%20Nervous%20Too%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20just%20Ukraine%2C%20America's%20European%20allies%20are%20also%20now%20nervous%20about%20the%20intent%20of%20Trump.%20Since%20the%20Second%20World%20War%2C%20they%20enjoyed%20the%20US%20security%20umbrella%20under%20NATO.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20now%20they%20are%20unsure%20if%20the%20US%20under%20Trump%20will%20honour%20Article%205%20of%20the%20NATO%2C%20which%20is%20triggered%20when%20a%20member%20state%20comes%20under%20attack.%20It%20implies%20that%20an%20attack%20on%20one%20member%20is%20an%20attack%20on%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20even%20fear%20in%20Europe%20that%20Donald%20Trump%20may%20sign%20a%20deal%20with%20the%20Russian%20leader%20Vladimir%20Putin%20that%20will%20lead%20to%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20US%20forces%20from%20Baltic%20states%20and%20effectively%20kill%20the%20NATO%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20could%20be%20similar%20to%20the%20non-aggression%20treaty%20signed%20by%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20Nazi%20Germany%20on%20August%2023%2C%201939%2C%20sending%20shockwaves%20to%20other%20European%20countries%20and%20prompting%20Hitler%20and%20Stalin%20to%20annex%20neighbouring%20countries.%20It%20is%20another%20matter%20that%20Hitler%20invaded%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20two%20years%20later%2C%20putting%20an%20end%20to%20the%20treaty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEuropean%20members%20of%20NATO%20may%20call%20themselves%20major%20powers%2C%20but%20they%20can't%20match%20Russia's%20military%20might%20without%20US%20support.%20Even%20after%20losing%20more%20than%20a%20hundred%20thousand%20men%20and%20lots%20of%20military%20equipment%20in%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%2C%20Moscow%20remains%20a%20strong%20power%2C%20mainly%20because%20of%20its%20nuclear%20arsenal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20Why%20Has%20Trump%20Changed%20The%20Narrative%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20always%20been%20an%20admirer%20of%20strongmen%20like%20Putin.%20Even%20during%20his%20first%20term%2C%20he%20developed%20a%20rapport%20with%20him.%20He%20also%20dislikes%20Zelenskyy%2C%20whom%20he%20sees%20as%20more%20of%20a%20roadblock%20in%20ending%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20former%20businessman%2C%20Trump%20sees%20things%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20profitable%20deals.%20Western%20sanctions%20have%20hit%20Russia%2C%20but%20American%20companies%20have%20also%20suffered%20business%20losses%2C%20running%20into%20billions%20of%20dollars.%20He%20would%20like%20to%20reverse%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20despite%20Ukraine's%20resistance%2C%20Trump%20believes%20Zelenskyy%20will%20have%20to%20give%20access%20to%20critical%20minerals%20in%20return%20for%20any%20future%20US%20support.%20Some%20in%20the%20Trump%20administration%20suggest%20Kyiv%20should%20provide%20Americans%20with%20those%20minerals%20in%20return%20for%20the%20US%20military%20and%20financial%20aid%20already%20received%20by%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20blamed%20European%20leaders%20for%20not%20doing%20enough%20to%20end%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%20He%20has%20also%20complained%20for%20a%20long%20time%20that%20Europe%20has%20lived%20off%20the%20US%20for%20too%20long%20and%20it%20must%20pay%20for%20its%20security.%20Europeans%20have%20increased%20their%20defence%20budgets%20but%20not%20enough%20to%20survive%20without%20US%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEuropean%20Plan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20face%20of%20changing%20US%20policy%20under%20Trump%2C%20European%20leaders%20are%20working%20on%20a%20plan%20to%20guard%20against%20a%20Russian%20attack.%20This%20involves%20a%20proposal%20to%20deploy%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20peacekeeping%20troops%20in%20Ukraine.%20The%20proposal%20has%20the%20support%20of%20Britain%20and%20France%20and%20is%20in%20response%20to%20Zelenskyy's%20request%20of%20100%2C000%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20idea%20doesn't%20have%20wider%20support%20in%20Europe.%20Germany%2C%20another%20big%20power%20in%20the%20continent%2C%20has%20already%20called%20it%20premature.%20The%20proposal%20has%20been%20dismissed%20by%20Russia%2C%20which%20currently%20has%20about%20600%2C000%20troops%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20Britain%20and%20France%2C%20with%20much%20smaller%20armies%20than%20Russia%2C%20can't%20send%20troops%20to%20Ukraine%20without%20some%20backup%20from%20the%20United%20States.%20And%20that%20looks%20unlikely%2C%20for%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20Ukraine%20envoy%2C%20General%20Keith%20Kellogg%2C%20who%20visited%20Kyiv%20and%20met%20Zelenskyy%20on%20Thursday%2C%20said%20all%20options%20must%20be%20open%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20outcome%20of%20peace%20talks.%20But%20he%20knows%20that%20any%20decision%20to%20provide%20any%20US%20military%20cover%20will%20be%20made%20by%20Trump%20who%20looks%20less%20inclined%20to%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Naresh%20Kaushik%20is%20a%20former%20editor%20at%20the%20Associated%20Press%20and%20BBC%20News%20based%20in%20London.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740298800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-11%2Ftrump-putin-650-afp_650x400_61510401801.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhas-trump-abandoned-ukraine-in-favour-of-russia-7774931%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20a%20former%20businessman%2C%20Trump%20sees%20things%20from%20the%20perspective%20of%20profitable%20deals.%20Sanctions%20have%20hit%20Russia%2C%20but%20American%20companies%20have%20also%20suffered%20business%20losses%20running%20into%20billions%20of%20dollars%20as%20a%20result.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fhas-trump-abandoned-ukraine-in-favour-of-russia-7774931%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Guru%20Randhawa%20gets%20injured%20while%20performing%20stunt%20on%20the%20sets%3A%20'Bahut%20mushkil%20kaam...'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740298363000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-118500650%2Cimgsize-26430.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2