%2C%20healthcare%2C%20livelihoods%2C%20and%20social%20justice%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBasera%20Samajik%20Sansthan%20(Noida)%20%E2%80%94%20Supporting%20HIV-positive%20individuals%20and%20vulnerable%20groups%2C%20including%20sex%20workers%2C%20MSM%20(men%20who%20have%20sex%20with%20men)%2C%20and%20transgender%20persons.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDeepshikha%20Samiti%20(Delhi)%20%E2%80%94%20Helping%20people%20with%20HIV%2FAIDS%20find%20employment%20and%20participate%20in%20governance.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EVikalp%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Group%20(Vadodara)%20%E2%80%93%20Working%20for%20the%20rights%20of%20marginalised%20women%20and%20gender%2Fsexual%20minorities%20in%20rural%2C%20tribal%20areas.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESappho%20for%20Equality%20(Kolkata)%20%E2%80%94%20Fighting%20for%20the%20rights%20and%20social%20justice%20of%20individuals%20with%20non-normative%20gender-sexual%20orientations%20and%20identities.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKarna%20Subarna%20Welfare%20Society%20(Murshidabad)%20%E2%80%94%20Building%20resilience%20within%20the%20LGBTQIA%2B%20community%20and%20generating%20sustainable%20livelihoods.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EYa_All%3A%20The%20Youth%20Network%20(Manipur)%20%E2%80%94%20A%20queer%2C%20youth-led%20organisation%20working%20on%20mental%20health%2C%20sexual%20health%2C%20and%20economic%20inclusion.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EChhattisgarh%20Mitwa%20Sankalp%20Samiti%20(Chhattisgarh)%20%E2%80%94%20Focused%20on%20the%20development%20and%20mobilisation%20of%20the%20transgender%20community.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPayana%20(Bengaluru)%20%E2%80%94%20Providing%20advocacy%20services%20and%20support%20to%20local%20sexual%20minority%20communities.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20goal%20is%20not%20just%20to%20give%20grants%20but%20to%20create%20a%20long-term%20funding%20ecosystem%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Parmesh%2C%20who%20identifies%20as%20gay%2C%20and%20has%20long%20advocated%20for%20workplace%20inclusivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20call%20for%20corporates%20and%20philanthropists%20to%20step%20up%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fund%E2%80%99s%20organisers%20are%20urging%20businesses%2C%20high-net-worth%20individuals%2C%20and%20corporate%20CSR%20initiatives%20to%20commit%20to%20sustained%20funding%20for%20LGBTQIA%2B%20causes.%20To%20attract%20diverse%20funders%2C%20they%20have%20created%20three%20tiers%20of%20donation%20categories%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECatalyst%20(Rs%2025-50%20lakh)%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIlluminator%20(Rs%2050%20lakh%2B)%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBeacon%20Circle%20(Rs%205%20crore%2B)%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CToday%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20challenges%20is%20that%20the%20critical%20connection%20%E2%80%94%20between%20the%20largest%20corporations%20and%20the%20neediest%20NGOs%20%E2%80%94%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20exist.%20Big%2C%20well-known%20LGBTQIA%2B%20organisations%20do%20get%20funding%20and%20resources%2C%20but%20if%20you%20want%20to%20ensure%20that%20your%20corporate%20money%20is%20reaching%20the%20most%20underfunded%20places%2C%20this%20fund%20is%20a%20bridge%20to%20see%20that%20happen%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Saurabh%20Kirpal%2C%20a%20senior%20advocate%20and%20LGBTQIA%2B%20rights%20crusader%20who%20was%20among%20the%20planners%20behind%20the%20Pride%20Fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20new%20chapter%20in%20queer%20philanthropy%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20India%E2%80%99s%20queer%20communities%2C%20the%20Pride%20Fund%20goes%20beyond%20providing%20financial%20support.%20It%20symbolises%20a%20long-awaited%20acknowledgement%20of%20their%20strength%2C%20a%20critical%20step%20toward%20sustainable%20change%2C%20and%20an%20opportunity%20to%20redefine%20the%20landscape%20of%20philanthropy%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20true%20equity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20grassroots%20organisations%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EPride%20Fund%3C%2Fem%3E%20arrived%20a